  <hr />

  <section id="overview">
    <h2>8.1 Overview</h2>
    <p>
      The <code>.rcan.yaml</code> file is the single source of truth for a robot's configuration. It is
      human-readable, version-controlled, and schema-validated. One robot = one config file.
    </p>
    <p>
      Implementations MUST validate configs against the JSON Schema published at
      <a href="https://rcan.dev/schema/rcan.schema.json" class="text-accent hover:underline">rcan.dev/schema/rcan.schema.json</a>
      before starting any runtime. A config that fails schema validation MUST prevent the runtime from starting.
    </p>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <section id="required-keys">
    <h2>8.2 Required Top-Level Keys</h2>
    <div class="not-prose overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full text-sm">
        <thead>
          <tr class="border-b border-border">
            <th class="text-left py-3 pr-4 text-text-muted font-medium">Key</th>
            <th class="text-left py-3 pr-4 text-text-muted font-medium">Type</th>
            <th class="text-left py-3 text-text-muted font-medium">Description</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {topLevelKeys.map(k => (
